Title: Six Simple Steps - Welcome to Microsoft 365
Description: Get started with Microsoft 365 in six simple steps. Sign in and get started at office.com, create and save files securely in the cloud, share files and collaborate with others in real time, work with your team in teams and channels with Microsoft teams, set up your mobile apps, and try new things.

Title: Get started with Teams
Description: Get started with Teams with seven simple steps. Get an overview of teams and channels, learn how to get your team up and running, work in channels, upload and share files, start and pin chats, join a Teams meeting, and manage meetings.

Title: Create a chat-based workspace with Teams
Description: When you have a place to create and make decisions as a team, there’s no limit to what you can achieve. Learn how to use Teams to bring everything together in a shared workspace where you can chat, meet, share files, and work with business apps.

Title: Create impactful content together
Description: Create impactful content together in Microsoft 365. Get an overview of Microsoft 365, learn how to sign in, create, save and share files, collaborate with others, move a file from OneDrive to SharePoint Online, and share a file or folder.

Title: Save and share files with OneDrive
Description: Learn how to save and share files with OneDrive. Get an overview of OneDrive, learn OneDrive basics, create and upload files and folders, Sync files and folders, and set up the OneDrive mobile app on your phone or tablet.

Title: Share sites and content with SharePoint
Description: Learn how to share sites and content with SharePoint. Get an overview of SharePoint Online, find and follow sites, news and content, create, upload and share files in a document library, sync files and folders, sync files with Files on Demand, and stay connected on your mobile device.

Title: Connect your organization with Yammer
Description: Connect your organization with Yammer. Get an overview of Yammer, learn how to sign in and edit your profile, set notifications, like, reply to, and share posts, post and update and attach files, join and create communities, and share files and community resources.

Title: Microsoft 365 Accessibility Overview and Resources
Description: Get started quickly with the Microsoft 365 accessibility overview and resources. Before sending your email or sharing a file, run the Accessibility Checker to make sure your content is accessible for people of all abilities to read and edit. See the Microsoft 365 accessibility intro, learn about the Accessibility Checker, and get accessible templates for Office.

Title: Create more accessible email messages in Outlook
Description: Create more accessible email messages in Outlook by ensuring that they are accessible to people with limited or no vision. Set HTML as the default message format, set a default font, create an accessible signature, add alt text to images, and create bulleted lists or tables to add structure that helps screen readers communicate order and relationships.

Title: Create more accessible Word documents
Description: Create more accessible Word documents with Accessibility Checker to check and correct accessibility issues. Add alt text to images and objects, use heading styles to improve accessibility, create meaningful file names and hyperlinks, organize information in tables to show relationships, and learn tips that make files more accessible for people with screen readers.

Title: Create more accessible Excel workbooks
Description: Create more accessible Excel workbooks using charts, tables, descriptive labels, and adding alt text to images and objects. Find and use an accessible template, explore accessible template features, and make your headings, labels, and worksheet names descriptive to make data accessible and understandable for everyone, including people with reading or vision disabilities.

Title: Create more accessible PowerPoint presentations
Description: Create more accessible PowerPoint presentations. Create slides with an accessible reading order, use accessible templates and fonts, and add alt text to charts, pictures, and other visuals Learn tips and best practices to make charts, graphs, and images more accessible for people who are color blind or have a vision or reading disability. Save your presentation in a format that can be read by a screen reader.

Title: Collaboration
Description: Do your best work together. With Microsoft 365, you can collaborate with anyone, anywhere. Learn how to share, co-author, comment, and meet with Microsoft 365 products and services.

Title: Run effective meetings
Description: Learn how to run effective hybrid meetings. Learn effective meeting tips, meeting considerations, what to do before, during, and after hybrid meetings, how to schedule, plan and lead effective meetings, follow a meeting checklist, engage your audience, and reduce meeting fatigue.

Title: Create inclusive meeting environments
Description: Learn how to create inclusive meeting environments, make meetings and related content accessible for all, limit distractions in meetings, and build empathy across time zone.

Title: Asynchronous collaboration and co-authoring
Description: Learn how to reduce or replace meetings with asynchronous collaboration and co-authoring. Learn best practices for collaborating in Microsoft 365, co-author shared files in Office apps, Teams, OneDrive, and SharePoint and troubleshoot common co-authoring errors.

Title: Reach large audiences with live events
Description: Reach large audiences with live events. Learn how to get started, plan and schedule a live event in Teams, and schedule a live event in Yammer.

Title: Stay well
Description: Stay well by practicing self-care tips for your personal well-being. Block your calendar for meals, breaks, and movement. Set your status in Microsoft Teams to indicate free or busy times. Connect with others in a Teams channel for social or work-related conversations. Manage notifications in Teams to determine how, when, and where your notifications appear. Turn on Focus assist in Windows 10 to avoid distractions when you need to focus.

Title: Stay connected
Description: Social capital and other measures of social connection are associated with better health and job satisfaction. To stay connected in a hybrid workplace, learn how to create social channels using Teams meetings and chat to host small group lunches, social hours, and other casual spaces that can mimic the “water cooler” in the office regardless of work location. Keep regularly scheduled 1:1s and consider splitting one 1:1 meeting into 2 shorter meetings throughout the week. Channel conversations in Teams are also a great way to keep the whole team in the know.

Title: Stay productive
Description: Set up your physical and virtual workspace for productivity. Learn which tasks and meeting types are better for hybrid work or in-person work so that you can plan your schedule ahead of time. Create focus time in Teams, set quiet hours and quiet days, and set a status message in Teams. For team productivity, decide which days are best for in-person meetings and what type of work can be done remotely. Also decide when meetings (in person or remote) are necessary and when are they optional.

Title: Use Microsoft 365 across your work and devices
Description: Use Microsoft 365 across your work and devices to stay connected, take and read notes, access your files on any device, create impactful content, save time, express yourself freely with digital ink, bring your work to life with 3D, make your work accessible, and stay secure and private at work.

Title: Use Microsoft 365 across your team
Description: Use Microsoft 365 across your team to create and organize teams, optimize team conversations, work together in Microsoft Teams, manage meetings, and collaborate on files.

Title: Use Microsoft 365 across your organization
Description: Use Microsoft 365 across your organization to set up your company’s network in Yammer, your company’s home base in SharePoint, and your company’s video portal in Microsoft Stream.

Title: Day in your digital life with Office 365
Description: Discover new ways to simplify your day in your digital life with Office 365. See how to start your digital day, tasks you can complete over your morning coffee, during your commute, meeting at the office, collaborating with colleagues, connecting across the company, and how to protect yourself from phishing.

Title: Cybersecurity fundamentals
Description: With cybersecurity fundamentals, learn what cybersecurity and multi-factor authentication are, firewall and network protection in Windows security, the dangers of oversharing, and how to secure your device to prevent changes security with Tamper Protection.

Title: Digital safety
Description: Get tips to keep your data safe with this digital safety module. Learn how to work from home more securely, collaborate in OneDrive, be safer over wireless connections, and protect your family online with Windows Security.

Title: Top threats
Description: Get tips to keep your data safe with this digital safety module. Learn how to work from home more securely, collaborate in OneDrive, be safer over wireless connections, and protect your family online with Windows Security.

Title: Work remotely with Microsoft 365
Description: Microsoft Teams and Office 365 help you get work done—with others and on your own—wherever you are today.

Title: Access Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Access Quick Start. Create a database, import data from Excel, add a primary key, backup your database, and create a split query, split form, or report.

Title: Intro to Access
Description: With Intro to Access, learn how Access can help you use templates to build databases quickly, find and report on data, create rich data entry forms, and import, transform, and export data sources. Learn database concepts and terms, good database design, and steps to create a database with database objects like tables, queries, forms, reports, macros, and modules.

Title: Create an Access database
Description: Learn how to create an Access database, whether to create a desktop database or an Access web app, the differences, and design considerations like IT requirements, access to data and design, and business goals and requirements. Create databases from a template, scratch, or an Access web app.

Title: Add tables
Description: Learn how to build tables and set data types

Title: Use relationships
Description: Use relationships in Access to harness the power of relational databases by combining data across tables. Learn about Relationships view, the types of relationships between tables, and how to edit relationships. Create relationships with the Lookup Wizard, the Relationships Pane, and learn how to create one-to-one and many-to-many relationships.

Title: Add and edit data
Description: Learn how to add and edit data in Access and take advantage of the streamlined editing, powerful querying, and helpful reporting capabilities by copying data from an Excel spreadsheet. If you maintain data in other sources, like Excel spreadsheets and SharePoint sites, you can also link to the data from your Access database, to always ensure you’re working with the latest data

Title: Manage data with queries
Description: Manage data with queries in Access to answer business questions, make bulk updates, or delete data from the database. Learn what queries are, how they’re used, and how to create queries. Learn how to create basic queries for quick search with Query Design and use joins, outer joins, and intermediate tables to create queries with more than one data source.

Title: Create forms
Description: If you often use the same set of forms and reports, you can create a navigation form in Access desktop databases to group them together. Learn how to add a form or report to the navigation form, change the label, apply a visual theme, and set the navigation form as the default display form.

Title: Create reports
Description: Learn how to create and format reports in Access so that’s easy to view and understand. Learn how to create basic reports using Access report tools, add grouping, sorting, or totals to report fields, add a theme or logo, highlight data with a conditional formatting rule, and print a report.

Title: Protect databases
Description: Protect your databases in Access. It’s a best practice to keep a regular backup of your database in the case of a system failure, a database is damaged or missing data, you need to review an older version, or you need to restore your database. Learn how to back up a database and restore a database with these simple steps.

Title: Create Charts
Description: Create charts in Access to display data in a useful visual format. Learn how to create and format a column chart, bar chart, line chart, pie chart, and combo chart.

Title: Excel Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Excel Quick Start guide. Learn how to create a workbook, enter data, save your workbook to OneDrive, automatically fill a column with Flash Fill, quickly calculate with AutoSum, create a chart, or use conditional formatting with Quick Analysis, freeze the top row, share your workbook to collaborate with others, and set up your mobile apps.

Title: Intro to Excel
Description: Check out this intro to Excel course to learn how to create a workbook, insert or delete a worksheet, move, copy, or print a worksheet, use Excel as a calculator, fill data automatically, and create a drop-down list.

Title: Rows & columns
Description: Use Excel rows and columns to organize your data. Learn how to insert or delete rows and columns, select content in Excel, freeze panes to lock rows and columns, hide or show rows or columns, filter for unique values or remove duplicate values, split text into different columns, and create a list of sequential dates

Title: Cells
Description: Learn how to work with Excel cells - move or copy cells, change the column width or row height, find or replace text or numbers on a worksheet, merge and unmerge cells, apply data validation to cells, and import or export text (.txt or .csv) files.

Title: Formatting
Description: Learn how to format in Excel to save time and make your worksheet useful for you and your team. Learn helpful tips like how to format numbers (currency, percentages, dates, phone numbers), use conditional formatting to provide visual cues, change or copy cell formatting, add a watermark, display or hide zero values, and create a custom number format.

Title: Formulas & functions
Description: Use Excel formulas and functions to perform calculations and solve problems. Learn how to use XLOOKUP, VLOOKUP, SUM, SUMIF, SUMIFS, COUNTIF, IF, IFS, and MATCH to find values, do calculations, save time, and manage data automatically.

Title: Tables
Description: Create and format tables in Excel to visually group and analyze data. Learn how to sort and filter data in a range or table, total data, and use slicers to filter data.

Title: Charts
Description: Charts in Excel helps you visualize your data in a way that creates maximum impact on your audience. Learn how to create a chart, add or remove titles, show or hide a chart legend, add or remove a secondary axis, add a trendline or sparkline to show data trends, and use Quick Analysis to pick the perfect chart.

Title: PivotTables
Description: Excel PivotTables are a powerful tool to calculate, summarize, and analyze data and see comparisons, patterns, and trends in your data. Learn how to create a PivotTable to analyze worksheets, tables, and ranges, use the Field List to arrange fields, group or ungroup data, sort data, filter data, and create a PivotChart.

Title: Share and coauthor with Excel
Description: Learn how to share and coauthor in Excel to collaborate with others in real time. See how to use comments and notes, collaborate in the same file at the same time, see files others have shared with you, lock or unlock specific areas of a workbook, protect an Excel file, and save or convert an Excel file to a PDF.

Title: Common uses of functions
Description: Automatically number rows, calculate the difference between two dates, define and use names in formulas, and combine text from two or more cells in one cell.

Title: Linked data types
Description: Learn how to use linked data types in Excel to get data on subjects like cities, foods, stocks, geography, and more. You can also get data types provided by your organization through Power BI.

Title: Get to know Power Query
Description: Get started with Excel Power Query and take your data transformation skills to the next level. Import data from the web or an Excel table. Set up a header row, convert a data type, or filter unnecessary rows. Split data into multiple columns or merge queries and join tables.

Title: Get started with Lists
Description: Get started with Microsoft Lists to track information and organize work. Create a list from the Lists app, create a list in a Teams channel, add or edit list items, create or change the view of a list, edit a list view, find and manage your lists, share a list or list item, and track business information.

Title: Microsoft 365 for business Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Microsoft 365 Quick Start. Learn how to create and work on files online, upload files to OneDrive, share files and folders, collaborate with others in real time, and set up your mobile apps to work from anywhere on all your devices.

Title: Get started with Microsoft 365
Description: Learn how to get started with Microsoft 365 to take your productivity to the next level. Get an overview of Microsoft 365 to work in Teams and the Office apps, collaborate with others, securely save your files in the cloud, stay connected, and achieve more with intelligent features. See how to sign in and get started at office.com.

Title: Create and save
Description: Create and save files using Microsoft 365. Learn how to create and save files the same way across Office apps using the Office desktop apps and office.com apps. Save files to the cloud using OneDrive and sync files with Files on Demand.Create and save files using Microsoft 365. Learn how to create and save files the same way across Office apps using the Office desktop apps and office.com apps. Save files to the cloud using OneDrive and sync files with Files on Demand.

Title: Share and collaborate
Description: Wherever you’re working in Microsoft 365, it’s simple to share and collaborate on your files. Learn how to share a file, set permissions, copy a link, collaborate and co-author on the same file at the same time, use @mentions to get someone’s attention, and use follow-ups to highlight areas you want to come back to, or pull others into the conversation.

Title: Work with Microsoft Teams
Description: Work with Microsoft Teams to collaborate with your team, help your team stay organized, and have conversations – all in one place. Learn how to create teams and channels, add a tab, pin a channel, create and format a post, start and pin a chat, make calls, join a Teams meeting, and learn tips and best practices to schedule, start, and run an effective meeting

Title: Get the most out of Windows
Description: Get the most out of Windows with tools to help you search and find documents. Learn how to use the Search bar, Task View, and File Explorer. Learn about Microsoft Edge, privacy settings, switching between languages, personalized tabs, Collections, and using Edge on your mobile device. Use Microsoft Search in Bing to get search results from the web and your organization.

Title: Work from anywhere
Description: With Microsoft 365, you can work from anywhere. Set us the OneDrive mobile app on your mobile device to access, upload, and share your files on your mobile device from anywhere. Set up the Outlook mobile app for iOS or Android to stay connected. Get the top 10 tips to help you save time and achieve more faster.

Title: Cool Microsoft 365 features
Description: Learn about cool Microsoft features. Create professional looking slides with PowerPoint Designer. Gain insights into your data through visual summaries, trends, and patterns with Analyze data in Excel for the web. Get spelling, grammar, and writing suggestions from Editor in Word. Learn how to make your content more accessible.

Title: Get started
Description: Learn how to get started with Microsoft Edge, including how to add a site to your favorites, how to find the settings/tools/internet options, or how to change your default search engine to Microsoft Edge. In addition, learn how to sign in to sync Microsoft Edge across devices or how to discover the accessibility features in Microsoft Edge.

Title: Privacy and security
Description: Learn more about how Microsoft Edge helps keep you safe when you browse the web, including configuring privacy settings, tracking prevention, InPrivate browsing, deleting browser history, blocking popups and deleting cookies.

Title: Personalize
Description: Learn how to personalize Microsoft Edge and make the browser your own, including changing your home page, adding extensions, using the dark theme, using other languages in Microsoft Edge, and increasing the text size.

Title: Forms Quick Start
Description: Build a form in minutes. Learn how to add questions to your form, define settings, share your form, and check results in just a few easy steps!

Title: Create a form and view results
Description: Learn how to use Forms to create surveys, quizzes, and polls, and easily see results as they come in.

Title: Share and collaborate
Description: Learn how to collaborate with colleagues on your quizzes and forms and share your quiz or form as a template for others to use independently.

Title: Teams Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Microsoft Teams Quick Start guide. Learn how to sign in to Teams, pick a team and channel, chat in Teams, start a new conversation, reply to a conversation, use emojis, memes, and GIFs, share a file, collaborate with @mention, check your Activity Feed, search for messages, people, or files, and set up your mobile apps.

Title: Intro to Microsoft Teams
Description: Microsoft Teams is a collaboration app that helps your team stay organized and have conversations—all in one place. With Intro to Microsoft Teams, get an overview of teams, channels, meetings, conversations, tabs, share files, collaborate real time, find files, add people to a chat, make a call, manage your calendar, schedule a meeting, join meetings, share content, record a meeting, view our activity feed, and use the command box to search for people, items, or apps.

Title: Start chats and calls
Description: Use Microsoft Teams to start chats and calls. Learn how to start one on one or group chats, make video and audio calls from chats, pin chats for quick access, make calls, hide chats, delete messages, and set up a delegate to make or answer calls on your behalf.

Title: Set up and customize your team
Description: Set up and customize your team in Microsoft Teams. Create a public or private team, add members, create a channel, and use manage team to find members, channels, settings, and apps for your team. See the go-to guide for team owners to add and remove members, add team owners, manage channels, and change team settings. You can also pin a channel and reorder your teams, to organize your teams list.

Title: Explore apps and tools
Description: Apps let you do more in Microsoft Teams. Learn how to explore apps and tools, add apps in tabs and messages, and use connectors for notifications that are useful for the whole channel. Learn useful tips like how to turn a file into a tab and how to use the command box to help you search, take quick actions, or launch apps.

Title: Collaborate in teams and channels
Description: Collaborate in teams and channels in Microsoft Teams. Learn how to create a public or private channel, pin a channel, add a tab, share a file, meet now, show and hide channels, customize channel notifications, reply to a message, like or save a message, use @mention, collaborate on or co-edit a file, start a conversation, send email to a channel, and create a plan with Planner.

Title: Work with posts and messages
Description: Work with posts and messages in Microsoft Teams. Learn how to create and format a post, post a message to multiple channels, get attention with @mention, and save a post or message.

Title: Search and find files
Description: Upload and find files in Microsoft Teams. Learn how to upload and share files, attach a file in a channel, upload a file to the Files tab, and find files that you recently viewed or edited, created or edited across channels, or downloaded from Teams.

Title: Set up and attend live events
Description: Hosting a large online event? Microsoft Teams live events is an extension of Teams meetings, enabling you to produce events for large online audiences with more control over video, audience interaction, and reporting. Learn how to create a live event, produce a live event, attend and participate in a live event, and moderate questions.

Title: Manage Meetings
Description: Learn tips and best practices to manage and run effective meetings in Microsoft Teams. Join a Teams meeting, create instant meetings with Meet Now, meet in a channel, view and schedule meetings, show your screen or PowerPoint slides during a meeting, and move around during a Teams meeting to check activity and keep working during a meeting. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Manage your activity feed
Description: Select the Activity icon in the Microsoft Teams left rail to manage your activity feed, which gives you a summary of everything that’s happened in the teams channels you follow. Learn how to filter your activity feed and manage your notification settings to control what notifications you receive, where you receive them, and how often.

Title: Teams on the go
Description: Start a 1:1 or group chat in the Microsoft Teams mobile app to talk privately or collaborate with a smaller group. Create a channel, join a meeting, use your activity feed, or manage notifications on the go,

Title: Manage team schedules with Shifts
Description: Learn how to manage team schedules with Shifts in Microsoft Teams to create, update, and manage schedules for your team. Managers can create and manage shift schedules, and review, approve, or deny requests. Frontline workers can use Shifts to view and manage their schedule and stay in sync with their team.

Title: Create and manage bookings
Description: Bookings in Microsoft Teams lets you track, manage, and organize your team's appointments and calendars all in one place. You can create a Bookings calendar and add team members to it, build new appointment types, and create and manage in-person and virtual visits for your staff and attendees.

Title: Create approvals
Description: Approvals in Microsoft Teams is a way to streamline all of your requests and processes with your team or partners. Learn how to create new approvals, view the ones sent your way, and see all of your previous approvals in one place.

Title: Get started
Description: Office.com is the best place to start, whether it's the start of the day or you're getting back to your work.

Title: Outlook for the web
Description: Outlook on the web makes it simple to keep your email, calendar, and contacts right at your fingertips. Here are a few of the great features to use. Send messages and share files to collaborate with others.

Title: Word for the web
Description: With Word for the web, create documents, add text, images, and art, and share your file to work with others — no matter where you are.

Title: Excel for the Web
Description: Excel for the web gives you the power of Excel on any device, from almost anywhere.

Title: PowerPoint for the web
Description: PowerPoint for the web gives you the ability to create, edit, and present presentations on any device, from almost anywhere.

Title: Share your documents
Description: Wherever you're working in Office 365, it's simple to share your documents.

Title: OneDrive Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the OneDrive Quick Start guide. Upload files and folders, use OneDrive in your browser or on your desktop, save and open files in your Office apps, create and manage files and folders, search, back up, and share files, manage access and permissions, copy links, change views, collaborate in OneDrive, set up your mobile apps to work on the go.

Title: Intro to OneDrive (work or school)
Description: Get started with OneDrive to access and edit files, share information, save your files to the cloud so you can work on files with others, and keep your files protected and backed up. Learn what OneDrive is, how to get started, how to use the Navigation pane and Toolbar, and how to set up your mobile apps. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Manage your files with OneDrive
Description: Upload files so you can manage your files in OneDrive and get to them from anywhere. Learn how to upload files and folders, create files and folders, delete and restore deleted files, delete files in the cloud, turn on OneDrive Backup, and restore your OneDrive. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Share and sync with OneDrive
Description: Learn how to share and sync in OneDrive for work or school. Share files and folders, sync OneDrive files and folders, manage disk space, and sync files with OneDrive Files On-Demand to get to all your files in OneDrive or SharePoint Online, without having to download them and use storage space on your device. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: OneNote Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the OneNote Quick Start. Create, open, and switch between notebooks. Take notes and add pages and sections. Share pages or an entire notebook to stay organized and collaborate with others. Set up your mobile apps to get to your files from anywhere.

Title: Intro to OneNote
Description: With OneNote, you can type notes or record audio, sketch or write ideas, add a picture, find notes, organize pages into sections and sections into notebooks, and share notebooks to view and contribute together. Watch this Intro to OneNote overview video and then learn how to sign in, add a new page or section, rename a page or section, open a different notebook, and customize OneNote.

Title: Take notes with OneNote
Description: With OneNote, take notes the way you want – type notes, write notes, convert handwritten notes to text, and even record audio notes. Insert pictures, files, and videos. Create as many pages, sections, and notebooks as you need.

Title: Format notes with OneNote
Description: Format notes in OneNote to get them to look just the way you want. Highlight text, create lists, indent text, align notes, and apply styles. Apply a background color to a page or section to make it more visually appealing. Insert and format a table to visually organize information.

Title: Draw and sketch with OneNote
Description: Draw or sketch in OneNote to bring your notes to life. You can select a pen, pencil, or highlighter, the thickness, and the color. Create shapes like a circle, triangle, or rectangle, or even draw shapes with your finger, pen, or mouse and OneNote will clean them up for you.

Title: Stay organized with OneNote
Description: To stay organized with OneNote, learn how to search for notes, narrow the search, and organize your notebooks. See how to show navigation panes, move a page from one section to another, copy a page to another section or notebook, and move or copy a section.

Title: Share and sync with OneNote
Description: Share and sync your entire OneNote notebook to collaborate with others. Select share, who you want to share with, and whether they can edit or only view your page or notebook. You can also lock or password-protect notebook sections that you want to keep private.

Title: OneNote on mobile devices
Description: Use OneNote on your mobile devices so you can connect and work with your notes wherever you are. Use OneNote on iOS, OneNote for Android, or OneNote Online.

Title: Outlook Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Outlook Quick Start guide. Learn how to add an email account, create and send email, use @mentions, show Focused inbox, manage your calendar and contacts, schedule an appointment using Scheduling Assistant, add a contact, collaborate in Outlook, share a file, set up an online meeting and shared notes, and set up your mobile apps.

Title: Set up and customize Outlook
Description: Need to set up and customize Outlook? Learn how Outlook can help you organize your email, manage and share your calendar, share files, stay connected, and add an outlook.com account, Microsoft 365 email account, or Gmail account.

Title: Create and send email
Description: Learn how to create and send email in Outlook, create an email signature, send and receive attachments, and retract or replace a sent email. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Manage email
Description: Learn how to manage your email in Outlook. Use Automatic Replies to auto-reply to messages, search and filter email, refine your searches, ignore conversations, and use Clean Up Conversation to clean up your inbox. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Organize your inbox
Description: Learn tips to organize your inbox. Learn how to set a Follow Up flag, view or remove Follow Up flags, set a reminder, find an Action Item, create color categories, assign a color category to an email message, create a folder, move messages into a folder, add a folder to Favorites, or create a rule.

Title: Contacts and tasks in Outlook
Description: Keep track of your contacts and tasks in Outlook. Learn how to add a contact, create a contact group, import Gmail contacts, export contacts, and create tasks and a to-do list.

Title: Outlook Calendar
Description: Learn how to use your calendar in Outlook to organize your schedule. Switch your calendar view between day, week, or month, create appointments and meetings, schedule an online meeting, share your calendar, import calendars, search for calendar items, use color categories and reminders so you never miss an important meeting, and turn on Shared Calendar preview.

Title: Manage your inbox
Description: Manage your inbox in Outlook mobile. Learn how to play your emails, RSVP to invites instantly, swipe left and swipe right to manage your inbox, sort messages into Focused and Other to focus on what matters, and use Android widgets to access the tools you use all day, every day right from your Android home screen.

Title: Manage your time
Description: Use Outlook mobile to manage your time, schedule meetings, and see when everyone is available. Use the meeting location assistant, send meeting availability, share your calendar, merge and combine calendars, and manage your notifications. Learn the top 10 Outlook mobile tips.

Title: People and connections
Description: Use Outlook mobile to manage your time, schedule meetings, and see when everyone is available. Use the meeting location assistant, send meeting availability, share your calendar, merge and combine calendars, and manage your notifications. Learn the top 10 Outlook mobile tips.

Title: Search and share
Description: Learn how to search in Outlook mobile, share files and photos, search your calendar by title, subject, email address, or event description, and use the Search icon to find email attachments.

Title: Planner Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Planner Quick Start. Learn how to sign in, create a plan, add people to a plan, set up buckets for tasks, add tasks, due dates, comments and attachments, view a plan’s progress and get email updates and notifications, and set up your mobile device to use Planner anywhere.

Title: Ideas for your board
Description: Get ideas for your board in Planner. Plan an event like a product launch, support customers, publish content, or track progress. See real life examples to get ideas for how you can use Planner.

Title: Use Planner
Description: Use Planner to organize your team, see progress reports, and track individual assignments. Learn how to build a plan, add buckets and tasks, assign tasks and due dates, and add a plan to Teams. Compare Planner to ToDo, use Schedule View to organize your tasks on a calendar and see your Planner schedule in Outlook calendar.

Title: PowerPoint Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the PowerPoint Quick Start guide. Create a presentation, add a slide, picture, shape, or chart, save to OneDrive, rename a presentation, use themes and PowerPoint Designer, add transitions and animations, share and collaborate with others, add comments, chat while editing, restore previous versions, use Presenter View and Notes, and set up your mobile apps.

Title: Intro to PowerPoint
Description: In this intro to PowerPoint course, learn how you can use PowerPoint to create presentations, add text, images, art, and videos, select a professional design with PowerPoint Designer, add transitions and animations, save to OneDrive to get to your files from anywhere, and share your work to collaborate with others.

Title: Slides and layouts
Description: Learn how to create slides and layouts in PowerPoint. Create a slide master, add, rearrange, duplicate and move slides, apply a slide layout, add color and design to your slides with themes, apply a template to a new presentation, get design ideas with PowerPoint Designer, and customize a slide master. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Text & tables with PowerPoint
Description: Want to learn about text and tables with PowerPoint? Learn how to insert WordArt, add a hyperlink to a slide, create a PowerPoint presentation from an outline, check spelling in your presentation, create and format a table, insert a linked Excel chart, add slide numbers, date and time, and set the text direction and position in a shape or text box.

Title: Pictures and graphics with PowerPoint
Description: Add pictures and graphics in PowerPoint to make your presentation visually engaging. Learn how to insert a picture, apply an artistic effect, add SmartArt, add a background picture or company logo, add charts and graphs, or insert icons.

Title: Present slideshows
Description: Learn how to present slideshows in PowerPoint. Add speaker notes to your slides, rehearse the time and delivery, record a slide show with narration, print your slides, handouts, or notes, and create a self-running presentation.

Title: Animation, video & audio
Description: Add animation, video and audio in PowerPoint to make your presentation more engaging and professional. Add transitions between slides, animate text or objects, use the Morph transition, insert a video, add audio or music, and record your screen and embed it in your presentation.

Title: Share and coauthor with PowerPoint
Description: Share and coauthor with others in PowerPoint in real time. Work with comments, share your presentation, save a presentation as a video, inspect a presentation to remove personal and confidential information, or save a presentation as a PDF.

Title: SharePoint Online Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Word Quick Start guide. Learn how to sign in to SharePoint, search and discover news and information, find your site, create a site, add a list or document library, use filters to modify what you see, add a page, add a web part, collaborate with others, open a document from a document library, share a document, sync files to your computer, and set up your mobile apps.

Title: Intro to SharePoint Online
Description: With this intro to SharePoint Online, learn how you can use SharePoint to build intranet sites, pages, document libraries and lists, find and follow sites and news, and stay connected on mobile. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Create sites, posts, and lists
Description: Create sites, posts, and lists in SharePoint Online to connect your team or organization. Care a Team site or Communication site, explore news, activity, and documents on your site, use, filter, and update lists to keep your team on track, add or remove a news post, and create a page to communicate ideas or information to your team. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Share and sync with SharePoint
Description: Create, share, and SharePoint files

Title: Sway Quick Start
Description: Create in Sway, Add Content, Design and Share, and Learn More

Title: Share and access Sway
Description: Learn how to share and access Sway. See how to share your Sway, add a password, set privacy settings, use accessibility features to make your Sway accessible, and learn Sway keyboard shortcuts.

Title: Add content to Sway
Description: Learn how to add content to Sway. Import content into Sway, search for content, add video and audio files, embed an Office file, form, or other content in Sway, add Focus Points, copy and paste cards, and use QuickStarter to create a Sway quickly.

Title: Customize Sway
Description: Customize Sway to remove the Sway informational footer, use Administrator settings, see file size limits, and get answers to frequently asked questions and Admin help for Sway.

Title: Word Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Word Quick Start guide. Learn how to create a document, add and format text, add pictures, shapes, SmartArt, and charts, save your document to OneDrive, design and edit using styles and themes, check spelling and grammar, find and replace text, share your document, collaborate with others, track and review changes, and set up your mobile apps.

Title: Intro to Word
Description: With this intro to Word, see how to create a document and use word to review and track changes, improve your spelling, grammar, and writing with Editor, save your documents to OneDrive to get to your files from your computer, tablet, or phone, and share your work to chat, comment, and collaborate with others wherever they are.

Title: Write and edit
Description: Do your best writing in Microsoft Word. Learn how to add and edit text, find and replace text, check grammar and spelling, show word count, and insert and remove hyperlinks.

Title: Lay out pages
Description: There are several useful options to lay out pages with Word. Learn how to change margins, create newsletter columns, change page orientation, add a border to a page, insert a header or a footer, insert page numbers, and insert a page break.

Title: Insert tables, pictures, and watermarks
Description: Learn how to insert tables, pictures, and watermarks in Word. Create a table, add a picture, insert an icon and WordArt, show or hide the ruler, rotate a picture or shape, and wrap text around a picture.

Title: Save and print with Word
Description: Learn how to save and print in Word. Save a file to OneDrive so you can get to it from anywhere, convert or save a Word document to a PDF, edit a PDF, print your document, print an envelope, create and print labels, or print labels for your mailing list.

Title: Share and coauthor with Word
Description: Learn how to share and coauthor in Word. Share a document, collaborate with others on your Word documents, insert or delete a comment, track changes, review and accept tracked changes, and use word on a mobile device. Watch this video training to see how.

Title: Use Word for school
Description: Write an equation or formula in Word, indent a paragraph, insert lines, create a bibliography, and insert footnotes and endnotes

Title: Improve accessibility and ease of use with Word
Description: Learn how to improve accessibility and ease of use in Word. Use a screen reader, use Learning Tools to help with reading fluency and comprehension, use Accessibility Checker to make documents accessible, and learn keyboard shortcuts to perform tasks quickly.

Title: Format text
Description: Learn how to format text in Word. Change the font, font size, font color, copy formatting with Format Painter, create a bulleted or numbered list, change the line spacing, and apply styles and themes to visually enhance the design of your Word document.

Title: Yammer Quick Start
Description: Get started quickly with the Yammer Quick Start. Sign in to Yammer and join community conversations, find out what's trending in your organization, and set up the Yammer mobile app to use Yammer on the go.

Title: Roll out a successful Yammer network
Description: Follow these tips and best practices to roll out a successful Yammer network. Get an overview of Yammer, plan your strategy, personalize a Yammer network, identify the right use cases, create a community, prepare for launch, educate users, drive ongoing engagement, integrate Yammer into Teams, SharePoint Online and Outlook, and measure success.

Title: Use Yammer every day
Description: Learn how use Yammer every day to engage with people, leaders, and communities in your organization and share knowledge. Get an overview of Yammer, change your Yammer profile and settings, start a conversation, work with posts, attach files, discover and join communities, use notifications to stay connected, work with announcements, and learn tips and best practices to get the most out of Yammer.

Description: Discover what's new/what's changed for the latest update of Microsoft 365 learning pathways

Title: Plan your learning content
Description: Review Learning Pathways content and content types. Decide what works for your organization.

Description: Learn how to customize the Learning Pathways site, how to hide and show content, and how to build custom playlists.
